  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Somalia: Strengthening Linkages between Formal Justice System and Traditional Dispute Resolution System to Improve Access to Justice</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) To enhance the capacity of the Ministry of Justice and Constitutional Affairs (MOJC) and NGOs to engage with TDR mechanisms. 2) To strengthen the accessibility and effectiveness of the justice system by improving knowledge of the traditional dispute resolution system and strengthening linkages between it and the formal justice system. 3) To strengthen the compatibility of customary systems with international and national law. 4) To promote stability in Somalia through the social reintegration of low-risk ex-fighters using TDR processes.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Direct beneficiaries: The MOJC TDR Unit, elders&apos; committees, NGOs.
Indirect beneficiaries: Somali citizens and the users of the justice system, with specific regard to women and children.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aimed to promote stability in Somalia by reintegrating low-risk disengaged combatants through traditional dispute resolution (TDR) processes and to strengthen accessibility and effectiveness of the the justice system by improving linkages between the formal and customary systems and strengthening the compatibility of customary systems with international and national law.</narrative>
  </description>
